net.sf.jmuserver.gs.muObjects
Class MuMap

java.lang.Object
  net.sf.jmuserver.gs.muObjects.MuMap

public class MuMap
extends java.lang.Object

MuMap represents the game entity known as map.
It provides means to encapsulate visibile objects and manipulate them in terms of spawn and movement.

Author:
Marcel
See Also:
MuObject, MuWorld

public void broadcastPacketWideArea(MuObject Client,

moveCharacter

public boolean moveCharacter(MuCharacter Who)
Moves a MuCharacter to a new coordinate. The action considers the player visibility range, and broadcasts movement, spawn and "forget" packets appropriately.
The method uses the new and old coordinates of the MuCharacter.

Parameters:
Who - The character to be moved
x - The new X coordinate
y - The new Y coordinate
Returns:
False if character is not allowed to move there, true otherwise

addObject

public boolean addObject(MuObject object)
The function adds the given object into the map, at the right position and region (MuMapPoint).
It includes broadcasting the appropriate "spawn" packets.

Parameters:
object - The MuObject to be added.
Returns:
False if the object is already on the map, true otherwise
